Argentine Stocks: Petroleo Brasileiro, Siderar and YPF Gain

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-12-01T20:50:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/argentine-stocks-petroleo-brasileiro-siderar-and-ypf-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 1.8 percent to 2,609.14.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)   gained 2.1 percent to 63
pesos, its fourth day of gains. The Brazilian state-controlled
oil company rose after the government eliminated a tax on
foreigners’ stock purchases.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)   advanced 3.7 percent to 23.80 pesos.
Argentina’s largest steelmaker has gained 12 percent in the two
days since Buenos Aires-based newspaper La Nacion reported that
the company may expand its plant in San Nicolas.  YPF SA (YPFD)   increased 1.5 percent to 165 pesos.
Argentina’s largest oil company was reiterated “outperform” at
Raymond James Financial Inc., which cited a potential
convergence between local cheaper gasoline prices and prices of
neighboring countries, according to an e-mailed note to clients.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
